Like, I know I have at least one song's worth of stuff to say about something, but when it comes to actually writing stuff out, I can only get a chorus, and maybe a verse. I feel like writing down notes is too clinical, like I'm writing a college essay. If I have to force myself to write stuff down, is what I'm writing even important to me? Do I just not have that many thoughts? Gorillaz have written, like, 6 songs about the exact same thing and I never feel like they're repeating themselves. What's their secret?
